      "relation_type": "PROMOTES",
      "condition": "When data is sparse in rural areas or privileges dominant demographics",
      "evidence": "This paper trains a semi-supervised model on only 100 urban-mask and 170 tree-canopy annotated images, with labeled data drawn from particular platforms and regions, while South America's cities span hugely heterogeneous climate/land-cover types. Such limited and unevenly distributed training data can privilege dominant data patterns, instantiating the biased-dataset feature that Track 1 links to social inequity.",
